# Dynamic Academic Library System Implementation Plan

## 1. System Overview
We are building a dynamic, version-controlled Academic Library for the 19 healthcare and Ayurveda programs. It will replace static PDFs with editable files (docx, pptx, xlsx) and rich-text content, supporting full CRUD capabilities with strict Role-Based Access Control (RBAC) and Audit Logging.

## 2. Database Schema Changes

### A. Modify existing [Program](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/models/Academic.ts#5-13) model
- Add `course_type: { type: String, enum: ['diploma', 'certificate'], required: true }`.
- Note: Diploma courses will organize documents by `semester`, while Certificate courses will organize by `module`.

### B. Create `LibraryCategory` Model
Categories to organize documents (e.g., "Syllabus", "Study Material", "Assignments").
```typescript
interface ILibraryCategory extends Document {
    name: string;
    semester_or_module?: number; // Nullable for common categories
    createdAt: Date;
    updatedAt: Date;
}
```

### C. Create `LibraryDocument` Model
The core document reference.
```typescript
interface ILibraryDocument extends Document {
    course_id?: mongoose.Types.ObjectId; // Nullable if is_common is true
    category_id: mongoose.Types.ObjectId;
    title: string;
    content?: string; // For rich-text content
    file_path?: string; // For uploaded files
    file_type: 'docx' | 'pptx' | 'xlsx' | 'rich-text';
    current_version: number;
    is_common: boolean; // If true, linked to all courses
    is_deleted: boolean; // Soft delete
    deleted_by?: mongoose.Types.ObjectId;
    deleted_at?: Date;
    createdAt: Date;
    updatedAt: Date;
}
```

### D. Create `DocumentVersion` Model
For maintaining version control history.
```typescript
interface IDocumentVersion extends Document {
    document_id: mongoose.Types.ObjectId;
    file_path?: string;
    content?: string;
    version_number: number;
    updated_by: mongoose.Types.ObjectId;
    previous_version_reference?: mongoose.Types.ObjectId;
    timestamp: Date;
}
```

### E. Integrate with Existing [AuditLog](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/models/AuditLog.ts#3-14)
- Add `'LibraryDocument'` and `'LibraryCategory'` to the `entityType` enum in [AuditLog.ts](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/models/AuditLog.ts).

## 3. Role-Based Access Control (RBAC) & Enforcement Rules
- **Root Admin** (`is_root: true`): Full control. Can perform permanent deletions if absolutely necessary (though soft-delete is preferred), and can view soft-deleted items.
- **Power Admin** (Standard `admin`): Can Upload, Download, and Edit documents. Editing a document automatically creates a new `DocumentVersion` and increments the `current_version`. When deleting a document, it performs a **Soft Delete** (`is_deleted: true`). They cannot permanently delete records.
- **Audit Logging**: Every Upload, Edit, and Delete action will generate an [AuditLog](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/models/AuditLog.ts#3-14) entry tracking the `user_id`, [action](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/models/FeePayment.ts#3-12), `old_value`, and `new_value`.

## 4. API Endpoints to Build
- `GET /api/admin/library/categories`
- `POST /api/admin/library/categories`
- `GET /api/admin/library/documents` (lists active documents, supports filtering by course/semester/module)
- `POST /api/admin/library/documents` (creates new document + initial version)
- `PUT /api/admin/library/documents/[id]` (updates document, creates new `DocumentVersion` linking to previous version)
- `DELETE /api/admin/library/documents/[id]` (Soft Deletes the document. Root Admin bypass can be implemented if required).
- `GET /api/admin/library/documents/[id]/versions` (retrieves version history)

## 5. Verification Plan
1. Create a Diploma document and verify it requires a semester.
2. Create a Certificate document and verify it requires a module.
3. Edit the document and verify a `DocumentVersion` is created and `current_version` increments.
4. Soft-delete the document as a standard admin and verify it is hidden from the main list but still exists in the DB.
5. Check the [AuditLog](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/models/AuditLog.ts#3-14) to ensure the library actions are recorded.
